From: Shannon Nelson <shannon.nelson@intel.com>
Date: Wed, 23 Apr 2014 04:49:54 +0000
Subject: [PATCH v3 326/474] i40e: set lan_veb index
Patch-mainline: v3.16-rc1
Git-commit: 1bb8b9358ee0f6b297c4f33ca0a3a45338b5205c
References: bsc#909484 FATE#317397

When the VEB is created for the basic LAN device and its VSIs, we need to
set the tracking lan_veb index for later use.

Change-ID: I66bb74993bbda3621ca557437cb4b3517f9b315b
Signed-off-by: Shannon Nelson <shannon.nelson@intel.com>
Tested-by: Kavindya Deegala <kavindya.s.deegala@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Jeff Kirsher <jeffrey.t.kirsher@intel.com>
Acked-by: David Chang <dchang@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/i40e/i40e_main.c |    2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/i40e/i40e_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/i40e/i40e_main.c
@@ -7727,6 +7727,8 @@ struct i40e_veb *i40e_veb_setup(struct i
 	ret = i40e_add_veb(veb, pf->vsi[vsi_idx]);
 	if (ret)
 		goto err_veb;
+	if (vsi_idx == pf->lan_vsi)
+		pf->lan_veb = veb->idx;
 
 	return veb;
 
